<TEXT>
a college chemistry student with a 
previous bomb conviction was charged with building a 35pound bomb 
strong enough to destroy anything within 150 yards authorities 
said 
university of north florida student christopher jones 25 was 
arrested thursday after a onemonth sting operation police said 
friday 
an undercover officer told jones he needed a bomb to blow up a 
car and kill someone said sheriff jim mcmillan that didnt 
seem to bother him a whole lot 
this is what we call a megabomb if this bomb had been 
detonated it could have caused substantial damage or death to 
anyone or any property within a 150yard radius said willi 
ellison an agent with the us bureau of alcohol tobacco and 
firearms 
the bomb 18 inches tall was built from a liquid propane tank 
which had been cut in half filled with chemical explosives and 
equipped with a fiveminute fuse ellison said 
jones was arrested thursday after the undercover officer paid 
300 for the device which was dismantled by bomb squad officers 
he faces 10 years in prison and a 250 fine if convicted of 
possessing an unregistered explosive 
jones was convicted of exploding two pipe bombs at a convenience 
store in 1985 and was placed on five years probation no one was 
injured 
