<TEXT>
italian police obtained important 
information about mafia activities by bugging tombs at a cemetery 
where family members and friends discussed vendettas newspapers 
reported sunday 
the information obtained in the operation helped authorities 
obtain orders restricting the movements of 19 people the papers 
said 
in accordance with new antimafia legislation passed last month 
police were granted permission to plant listening devices in tombs 
at the ercolano cemetery near naples where several suspected 
members of the camorra were recently buried 
the camorra is the neapolitan version of the sicilian mafia 
police monitored plans of vendettas contracts and other 
clandestine operations in the conversations and prayers of widows 
other relatives and friends of the deceased the accounts said 
ercolano a town a halfmile from naples is the site of roman 
archaeological excavations it also is the site of intense camorra 
activity 
two clans have been feuding in the area since last february 
when five bandits looted archaeological sites taking away more 
than 200 priceless artifacts 
