the czechoslovak airline csa on sunday 
became the first foreign airline to resume flights to beirut since 
the city was reunified and the warring militias withdrawn 
civil aviation sources said a csa tupolev jet carrying 65 
passengers landed at beirut in the morning resuming the airlines 
weekly service after a threeyear suspension 
the soviet aeroflot bulgarias balkan airlines and syrian arab 
airlines were the only carriers to maintain flights to beirut in 
recent years most of the others suspended their flights after 
terrorist attacks by moslem shiite extremists in 1984 
security conditions have improved in beirut since the 
reunification of the city and the withdrawal of warring moslem and 
christian militias 
reunification was the first step in an arab leaguebrokered plan 
to end lebanons 15 years of civil war 
civil aviation sources said they were hopeful that western 
airlines would resume flights to beirut next year 
